01/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The NATO exercise dubbed Co-operative Key 2003 starts on Monday (1 September) at the military base in Plovdiv. 
This is the second time Bulgaria is hosting the exercise since 2001. 
Eight NATO member countries are participating, along with the six NATO invitees, including Bulgaria and Romania, as well as six partner nations, including Croatia and Macedonia.
In other news, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov has asked parliament to quickly adopt amendments to anti-crime legislation. 
Admitting passage of the bills would not be easy and would likely involve prolonged debate, he urged lawmakers to give the amendments priority status. 
(BTA, Trud, Dnevnik, 24 Chassa - 01/09/03; BTA, BNT - 31/08/03)
